    "While RNNs are useful for modeling sequences, they often struggle with long-range dependencies due to the vanishing and exploding gradient problems, where gradients can diminish or grow exponentially during backpropagation, making it difficult for the network to learn long-term dependencies effectively (Schmidt 2019; Staudemeyer and Morris 2019).",
    "Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks extend RNNs by introducing memory cells that can maintain information over long periods (see Fig. 6B) (Staudemeyer and Morris 2019).",
